WEBVTT

00:02.850 --> 00:08.818
you're listening to a teaching from Reality LA.

00:08.838 --> 00:09.860
I'm excited to be with you guys.

00:09.880 --> 00:13.725
We're concluding our four week essentials series today.

00:13.785 --> 00:17.731
And we're talking about what it means to serve in some capacity.

00:18.452 --> 00:20.715
So I want to start off real quick with a little story.

00:20.755 --> 00:21.897
I read a book recently.

00:21.937 --> 00:27.004
And part of the story, there was this man who collapsed on a city sidewalk.

00:27.645 --> 00:31.570
And dozens and dozens of people just walked right by him.

00:32.258 --> 00:34.561
And some people would slow down and look.

00:35.782 --> 00:38.965
But for a long stretch of time, nobody stopped.

00:39.006 --> 00:41.308
Nobody actually did anything to help.

00:42.409 --> 00:47.655
And then later, when people were interviewed and asked about this scenario, not one of the people said, I didn't care.

00:47.695 --> 00:52.661
Some people said things like, oh, I assume somebody else had it handled.

00:53.982 --> 00:55.784
Or I didn't know what to do in that situation.

00:55.864 --> 00:56.565
Or I couldn't stop.

00:56.585 --> 00:57.426
I had to be somewhere.

00:58.274 --> 01:04.946
And the story stuck with me because the onlookers in that story were not unusually cruel.

01:05.628 --> 01:07.932
They were painfully normal.

01:10.396 --> 01:19.954
It reveals this uncomfortable truth that it's possible to notice needs and to feel concern and to even believe the right things and then still keep moving.

01:21.186 --> 01:30.919
And it unearths this really important question that we need to be asking as well, which is what does real living faith do when it encounters real needs?

01:32.061 --> 01:33.262
That's what we're gonna dig into today.

01:33.303 --> 01:37.288
In James chapter two, starting in verse 14, if you have your Bibles, you can head there.

01:37.328 --> 01:50.546
We're gonna start in verse 14, and it's gonna press us a little bit on that question, not to shame us, not to guilt us into action, but to lovingly expose to us the difference between the kind of faith that sounds right

01:51.170 --> 01:52.912
and the kind of faith that is alive.

01:54.193 --> 01:56.075
So let me read the scripture for us and then we'll pray together.

01:57.076 --> 02:05.504
James 2 starting in verse 14, what good is it, my brothers, if someone says he has faith but does not have works, can that faith save him?

02:06.424 --> 02:17.515
If a brother or sister is poorly clothed and lacking in daily food, and one of you says to them, go in peace, be warm and filled without giving them the things needed for the body, what good is that?

02:18.596 --> 02:20.818
So also, faith by itself

02:21.154 --> 02:23.256
if it does not have works is dead.

02:24.818 --> 02:25.318
Let's pray together.

02:28.501 --> 02:29.923
Father in heaven, we love you.

02:30.583 --> 02:34.828
We love you and our greatest desire is to love you with all of our heart and soul and mind and strength.

02:35.468 --> 02:49.202
And so we pray and ask God today that the truth of your word with lovingly, gently, convict our hearts away from the temptations of comfort and of ease and lead us towards this

02:49.410 --> 02:51.754
Call to sacrificial service that you've given to us.

02:51.954 --> 02:55.059
Not out of guilt, not out of shame, but as a response to love.

02:56.601 --> 02:58.103
And so, God, our prayer is simply like, help us.

02:58.945 --> 02:59.806
Help us to do that, Lord.

02:59.826 --> 03:02.230
We pray these things in your mighty name, Jesus.

03:02.991 --> 03:04.874
And everybody said, amen.

03:05.595 --> 03:05.955
Amen.

03:06.857 --> 03:10.642
All right, I need to, it's gonna be a slightly untraditional start here to the sermon.

03:11.223 --> 03:15.269
I wanna lay out the gospel here right at the beginning, okay?

03:15.730 --> 03:18.354
The preaching books are like, no!

03:18.498 --> 03:20.481
But I'm the bad boy of the reality la teaching team.

03:20.501 --> 03:21.122
What can I say?

03:23.606 --> 03:24.929
Or this is why I preach two times a year.

03:24.969 --> 03:25.449
We'll find out.

03:28.034 --> 03:28.374
No.

03:29.196 --> 03:30.277
But listen, we got to start here.

03:30.317 --> 03:33.863
It is imperative to start here because this is absolutely foundational.

03:33.923 --> 03:36.848
And I don't want James too to confuse us right from the beginning.

03:37.229 --> 03:40.314
It is not what you do for God that saves you.

03:41.336 --> 03:45.202
You do not and you cannot earn your way to God.

03:45.794 --> 03:51.644
as one of the primary distinctions between Christianity and every other system of belief.

03:52.986 --> 03:58.134
Everything else says, work your way to God or to salvation or to some sense of worthiness.

03:58.595 --> 04:02.081
But Christ says, you are sinful and you are imperfect.

04:02.141 --> 04:06.388
You cannot earn your way back to me, but I will come to you.

04:07.430 --> 04:09.974
All you need to do is belief.

04:09.994 --> 04:12.498
All you need to do is trust in me.

04:13.058 --> 04:20.128
This is throughout Scripture, Romans 3, 28, for we hold that one is justified by faith apart from works of the law.

04:21.510 --> 04:26.417
Ephesians 2, 8 and 9, for by grace you have been saved through faith.

04:27.198 --> 04:33.507
And this is not your own doing, it is the gift of God, not a result of works so that no one may boast.

04:34.168 --> 04:41.458
Okay, you are saved by the grace of God through faith in Jesus, full stop, no additions to that, nothing else.

04:41.826 --> 04:46.472
If you hear anything contrary to that alarm bells, better go off in your mind.

04:47.994 --> 04:55.725
So James 2 right here, it's not asking if faith does or does not save, it's asking what kind of faith are we talking about here?

04:57.327 --> 05:03.175
And for James, when he says faith by itself, he's talking about a false kind of faith.

05:04.256 --> 05:11.346
It's not that true faith doesn't save, it's that the wrong faith, that faith, as he says in verse 14, cannot save.

05:12.418 --> 05:19.125
And what he's addressing is this professed only faith, a correct sounding faith.

05:19.766 --> 05:30.057
He's warning us there is a faith that can exist at the level of intellectual agreement, or theological correctness, or even religious language, but never take root in the heart.

05:31.598 --> 05:35.282
A couple verses later in verse 19, it says, even demons believe in God.

05:35.703 --> 05:36.924
They know who God is.

05:37.665 --> 05:38.706
It's not a knowledge thing.

05:40.066 --> 05:49.019
And James doesn't say that this kind of faith is imperfect, he doesn't call it flawed, and verse 17, he says this professed only faith by itself is dead.

05:50.021 --> 05:52.144
It is like a body that has no breath in it.

05:53.827 --> 05:57.032
It is disobedience that's dressed up as spirituality.

05:59.676 --> 06:02.820
Think back to when Jesus told the parable of the good Samaritan.

06:03.742 --> 06:09.330
There's a man who's beaten, he's left for dead on the side of the road, and a priest, he sees him,

06:09.538 --> 06:11.100
He acknowledges the need, but what does he do?

06:12.422 --> 06:14.765
He walks right by, goes to the other side of the street.

06:15.746 --> 06:19.491
And then a Levite, another religious leader, he sees them and he does the same thing.

06:21.213 --> 06:28.843
And so it takes a man who would have been considered this beaten man's enemy, a Samaritan man filled with compassion to stop and to help.

06:29.804 --> 06:37.714
And look, it wasn't that the Levite and the priest didn't know about God's compassion, they didn't lack theology, they lacked a transformed heart.

06:39.778 --> 06:46.808
So no, works don't save people, but a lack of works are a demonstration of a lack of saving faith.

06:48.390 --> 06:54.078
And verse 15 and 16 paint a picture of what faith without works looks like in everyday life.

06:55.219 --> 07:01.047
It doesn't deny needs, it notices them, but then keeps moving without stepping towards them.

07:02.750 --> 07:08.818
It speaks with this language of compassion without ever dignifying the person in front of them.

07:10.210 --> 07:14.517
And it offers words like, I'll pray for you, or be blessed.

07:14.537 --> 07:18.523
Not as a promise of presence, but as a way of avoiding cost.

07:20.826 --> 07:24.492
And this honestly, this is the stuff that people outside of the church pounce on.

07:25.093 --> 07:25.573
And you know what?

07:25.674 --> 07:26.094
Fair enough.

07:27.296 --> 07:30.060
When it's accurate, we need to repent of this posture.

07:31.162 --> 07:39.154
The 2024 Barna study concluded the primary reason that people resist Christian belief today is the hypocrisy of religious people.

07:41.506 --> 07:46.673
A lifeless faith is gonna undermine and discredit to a world who's watching.

07:49.016 --> 07:54.584
And so listen, orthodoxy is great, but orthodoxy without obedience, it's just spiritual noise.

07:56.747 --> 08:06.661
So you gotta ask yourself, can your life be characterized as one that is filled with spiritual language and intention, but bears no fruit of that faith?

08:08.203 --> 08:10.546
Is your faith alive, or is it dead?

08:12.962 --> 08:16.766
Because the response that James critiquing right here, it's not human cruelty.

08:18.027 --> 08:19.468
It's polite spirituality.

08:21.770 --> 08:22.431
Go in peace.

08:22.831 --> 08:23.512
Be warmed.

08:23.932 --> 08:24.493
Be filled.

08:24.653 --> 08:25.294
That's not harsh.

08:26.235 --> 08:27.175
That's not unkind.

08:27.336 --> 08:28.457
It's probably genuine.

08:30.138 --> 08:31.780
It's not an evil response.

08:31.900 --> 08:32.901
It's an incomplete one.

08:35.283 --> 08:37.545
So we hear this and we're like, OK, got it.

08:37.605 --> 08:38.726
It can't just stay theoretical.

08:39.087 --> 08:40.108
Real faith goes on the move.

08:40.128 --> 08:41.069
So let's go.

08:41.209 --> 08:41.829
Let's get to work.

08:41.949 --> 08:42.610
Time to move.

08:43.362 --> 08:45.124
Love the impulse, slow your roll a little bit.

08:46.225 --> 08:49.309
Because we can't just swing the pendulum all the way to the other side either.

08:49.669 --> 08:54.135
Because as much as you can know God, but never live for God, Scripture is also clear.

08:54.415 --> 08:56.578
You can serve God without ever knowing God.

08:57.899 --> 09:00.282
You can do the right things for the wrong reasons.

09:01.063 --> 09:04.647
You can perform good actions with all of the wrong motivation.

09:06.209 --> 09:07.090
Matthew 7,

09:07.458 --> 09:08.620
speaks of this most clearly.

09:08.660 --> 09:18.153
It talks about people doing all sorts of mighty works in the name of God, but then it concludes with Jesus saying, and then will I declare to them, I never knew you, depart from me.

09:18.594 --> 09:20.256
You workers of lawlessness.

09:22.199 --> 09:23.982
Ah, it should be terrifying.

09:25.965 --> 09:28.608
Listen, God does not just want religious performers.

09:30.471 --> 09:35.378
I remember back in elementary school, we had this thing called Random Acts of Kind this week,

09:35.650 --> 09:40.515
where we would basically track all the good, helpful, moral things that we would do.

09:40.555 --> 09:42.918
And then we'd turn it in at the end of the week.

09:43.218 --> 09:45.300
And my friends, it was mayhem.

09:45.761 --> 09:46.341
Mayhem.

09:46.762 --> 09:50.306
You have never seen so many self-righteous third graders in your life.

09:51.667 --> 09:52.548
Myself included.

09:52.608 --> 09:57.954
I would rake my neighbor's leaves and immediately turn to my friend and be like, you suck.

09:59.796 --> 10:01.778
I'm like, what?

10:02.850 --> 10:05.975
Like it was like, it was competitive kindness at that point.

10:07.357 --> 10:11.002
And listen, it may have produced good actions, but it created little monsters.

10:11.202 --> 10:16.710
You know, we were completely detached from the correct motivation behind why we were doing those things in the first place.

10:17.631 --> 10:26.204
And so as much as we are called to good works for God, we also need to remember God doesn't just want a result while missing out on the heart.

10:26.825 --> 10:27.666
That's not the point either.

10:29.346 --> 10:43.931
And when it is, when service is not rooted in Christ and not rooted in good news, its motivational engine becomes fueled by morality or approval or guilt or need to feel meaningful in some way.

10:45.173 --> 10:53.106
And then it quickly will just turn into this performance-based, selective, exhausting, works-for-love exchange.

10:55.490 --> 11:06.245
And when that happens, we become tempted to turn people into projects, to turn obedience into spiritual leverage, and to turn serving into a religious activity.

11:07.607 --> 11:16.199
And in the process, we burn out, or we build up pride or resentment, and we ignore real actual heart level needs.

11:18.242 --> 11:24.210
And so James is telling us words without actions are hollow, but he's also not calling us to religious activity apart from faith.

11:24.834 --> 11:25.375
So what is it?

11:25.655 --> 11:26.917
It's not faith without works.

11:27.698 --> 11:29.240
That's like a tree that bears no fruit.

11:30.501 --> 11:34.146
But it's also not works without faith or faith plus works for salvation.

11:34.226 --> 11:36.729
That's like fruit that grows from a rotten core.

11:38.051 --> 11:41.876
It's faith that produces works.

11:42.217 --> 11:46.723
Works don't save, but saved people work.

11:46.743 --> 11:49.426
Works don't save, but saved people work.

11:49.826 --> 11:52.108
Ephesians two really helps us here, verses eight through nine.

11:52.128 --> 11:55.552
They made it clear, save by grace, by faith, not by works.

11:55.812 --> 12:05.642
But then verse 10 follows immediately, for we are His workmanship created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand that we should walk in them.

12:07.084 --> 12:12.890
So these good works, they're not the root of salvation, they're the fruit of salvation.

12:14.572 --> 12:16.914
They're not the cause, they are the evidence.

12:18.178 --> 12:20.580
As I've heard it said, living faiths like gravity.

12:21.321 --> 12:23.563
You don't see gravity, but you can definitely see its effects.

12:24.785 --> 12:25.265
You feel it.

12:25.285 --> 12:34.094
And so true faith in the gospel is going to produce hearts and lives postured towards sacrificial service on God's mission.

12:35.695 --> 12:40.240
And that's because it looks to and it's empowered by a God who serves us first.

12:42.042 --> 12:46.546
James is not asking us to be something that God is not already himself.

12:47.650 --> 12:50.913
This is from beginning to end in your Bible.

12:51.814 --> 12:55.878
It reveals a God whose character is love expressed through action.

12:57.720 --> 13:00.243
We see this, I mean, you see this within God himself.

13:00.703 --> 13:02.365
The Father sends the Son.

13:02.425 --> 13:05.448
The Son willingly gives of himself.

13:06.309 --> 13:08.751
The Spirit humbly glorifies the Son.

13:09.171 --> 13:15.858
Every direction you look in the Trinity, God's life is marked by joyful and sacrificial love.

13:17.570 --> 13:24.199
And so when God calls us to serve, he's inviting us to simply reflect who he is, to reflect his character.

13:26.462 --> 13:30.908
And we see this again, all throughout scripture, but this culminates in the person of Jesus Christ.

13:32.310 --> 13:35.895
Jesus came and he proclaimed the kingdom of God.

13:36.616 --> 13:46.770
He spoke of the kingdom of God, but he also healed the sick, fed the hungry, restored the outcast, wept with the mourners, dignified the ignored,

13:47.778 --> 13:49.600
He witnessed in word and deed.

13:51.543 --> 13:53.145
I know you're waiting for this one in the serve sermon.

13:53.305 --> 14:02.756
Mark 1045, okay, for even the son of man came not to be served, but to serve and to give his life as a ransom for many.

14:03.878 --> 14:10.706
And that word that's used there to serve, Diaconneo, my pronunciation, I'm doing my best.

14:11.138 --> 14:18.986
That word, it was used to describe these low status roles in society, things like waiters, or household assistants, or messengers.

14:19.346 --> 14:30.677
And so when Jesus says this, when he says the son of man came to Diaconneo, he's actually completely redefining what it means to be great, what it means to have authority and power.

14:30.998 --> 14:37.304
And he's doing that by fusing together these two categories that Jewish people had kept separate.

14:37.985 --> 14:39.506
One is the son of man.

14:39.778 --> 14:43.684
from Daniel 7, this exalted ruler, this powerful Messiah.

14:43.704 --> 14:52.797
And the other is the suffering servant from Isaiah 53, the one who would bear sin, who would lay his life down for the sake of his people.

14:54.700 --> 15:01.390
And that fusion will come to its greatest climax in the ultimate sacrificial service of the cross.

15:02.992 --> 15:04.114
Philippians 2, it's one of my

15:04.226 --> 15:05.728
absolute favorite passages in Scripture.

15:05.928 --> 15:07.109
I think it details it beautifully.

15:07.589 --> 15:31.954
It says, being born in the likeness of men and being found in human form, he humbled himself by becoming obedient to the point of death, even death on a cross.

15:33.506 --> 15:41.074
This is the true power of God, is that we have a king of the universe who would serve unto death.

15:43.697 --> 15:48.842
Listen, the world's gonna tell us that power is to wipe the floor clean with your enemies.

15:50.784 --> 15:54.748
But Jesus says power is to get onto the floor and wipe your enemies' feet.

15:57.131 --> 16:00.114
So we work, we serve, not to imitate some

16:00.194 --> 16:08.622
abstract ideal or to do the right moral thing, but as a response to grace, as a reflection of the God who has already served us first.

16:10.704 --> 16:18.131
And then when our faith is in Christ, when we trust in Jesus, we become servants who then serve in a multitude of ways.

16:19.872 --> 16:27.860
So in Christ, a living faith will serve with a new identity and with a new heart and with new motivations.

16:29.121 --> 16:30.002
Listen, guilt,

16:30.402 --> 16:33.925
Fear, ego, comfort, comparison.

16:34.005 --> 16:39.070
Those might be powerful motivators in the moment, but they are terrible masters.

16:40.512 --> 16:43.935
They can drive you for a little while, but they will not sustain you.

16:45.236 --> 16:49.640
They will eventually burn you out, leave you empty, and steal your joy.

16:50.981 --> 16:55.225
But the gospel comes in and it changes the whole fuel source for you.

16:56.286 --> 16:58.709
In Christ, acceptance is already yours.

16:58.949 --> 17:00.050
Your salvation

17:00.130 --> 17:03.715
is secure and so you don't serve to become loved.

17:04.356 --> 17:06.199
You serve because you already are.

17:06.219 --> 17:08.281
That is who you are.

17:08.942 --> 17:11.506
Jesus hasn't just given us tasks to do.

17:11.546 --> 17:13.449
He's telling you who you are.

17:15.792 --> 17:17.995
James two, it's not guilting you into doing these things.

17:18.276 --> 17:22.682
It's trying to invite you or to re-invite you into a given identity.

17:23.082 --> 17:25.225
You are a child of God.

17:26.487 --> 17:28.530
And then God reminds you

17:28.674 --> 17:30.156
What a child of God does.

17:30.216 --> 17:32.118
It serves.

17:33.680 --> 17:37.023
So when your heart changes, everything will change.

17:37.584 --> 17:38.665
And you don't have to serve.

17:38.745 --> 17:40.087
You get to serve.

17:40.107 --> 17:41.228
You get to participate.

17:42.269 --> 17:43.130
And it's not from guilt.

17:43.210 --> 17:44.291
It's not from condemnation.

17:44.372 --> 17:45.753
It's not from comparison.

17:45.993 --> 17:51.159
It's out of freedom and gratitude that we serve.

17:51.179 --> 17:55.544
Second in Christ, we also serve sacrificially, okay?

17:55.564 --> 17:57.266
You're serving not destructively,

17:57.986 --> 18:02.452
Not to the point of burnout, but we will serve absorbing real costs.

18:03.934 --> 18:08.961
And we need to recognize our default as human beings is self-preservation.

18:09.903 --> 18:14.509
We have been trained to protect our time and our capacity and our comfort.

18:15.811 --> 18:23.762
And all of us, I don't doubt this at all, I think all of us wanna live lives of purpose and of meeting until it costs us something.

18:25.826 --> 18:28.269
The priest and the Levite didn't hate the wounded man.

18:28.309 --> 18:30.272
They just had somewhere else to be.

18:32.755 --> 18:40.405
One of the greatest barriers that we have in serving isn't hostility, it's distraction or consumption or hurry.

18:42.568 --> 18:53.522
So look, crowded schedules can feel really virtuous and justified, but sometimes it is just a socially acceptable way to avoid obedience.

18:55.682 --> 18:58.405
Living faith is gonna confront that selfishness.

18:59.246 --> 19:08.117
It's one of the primary ways that God disciples us out of self-centered living and exposes these quiet idols that we have of busyness and of self-importance.

19:09.779 --> 19:16.927
So you gotta ask yourself, what do I need to stop doing to have the margin to love my neighbor and the way that God has called me to?

19:20.051 --> 19:22.834
Okay, third, in Christ, we serve

19:23.138 --> 19:26.102
with a dignity-driven posture and perspective.

19:27.864 --> 19:32.310
We know, just like James 2 describes, we were once spiritually poor.

19:33.231 --> 19:34.532
We are exposed.

19:34.593 --> 19:35.394
We are in need.

19:35.614 --> 19:39.379
And God didn't just say to us, go in peace, figure it out on your own.

19:39.679 --> 19:40.901
He moved towards us.

19:41.702 --> 19:43.804
And so we now move towards others.

19:45.827 --> 19:46.548
Not as saviors.

19:46.648 --> 19:51.474
We are not the saviors in this situation, but as fellow image bearers with one another.

19:52.706 --> 20:03.960
And so when we talk about dignity-driven ministry, what we're saying is it's a ministry that recognizes and affirms the God-given dignity that's already present in every person.

20:05.161 --> 20:09.707
It refuses to operate out of this place of superiority or with this pity mindset.

20:10.849 --> 20:15.795
In God's kingdom, people aren't problems to deal with or projects to fix.

20:16.035 --> 20:17.737
They're image-bearers to love and to serve.

20:20.200 --> 20:21.682
And it doesn't deny.

20:21.762 --> 20:26.107
that there are real needs, it just refuses to define people by the need.

20:27.369 --> 20:30.733
We learn to see people's humanity before we see their hardship.

20:32.595 --> 20:37.982
And it's precisely because humans are made in the image of God that we do.

20:38.042 --> 20:39.905
We seek healing when people are wounded.

20:39.925 --> 20:43.689
We seek justice when dignity is being violated.

20:44.670 --> 20:50.738
We seek renewal where people feel forgotten and we seek restoration where brokenness has taken root.

20:52.802 --> 21:04.436
And listen, we're to do this wisely and we wanna do this humbly, not driven by outrage cycles or cultural pressures, but we are rooted in God's word and in God's heart and we seek these things.

21:06.539 --> 21:13.607
The parable of the Good Samaritan, it begins with a question, a lawyer comes to Jesus and he asks him, who is my neighbor?

21:14.829 --> 21:18.333
But the lawyer is not curious to the answer to that question.

21:18.413 --> 21:21.076
He's actually just trying to draw boundaries for himself.

21:21.597 --> 21:22.578
He's trying to figure out,

21:22.658 --> 21:24.341
Who can I avoid?

21:25.904 --> 21:28.728
And Jesus, wisely as he does, reframes the question.

21:29.289 --> 21:31.814
He says, who do you see as an interruption in your life?

21:32.896 --> 21:33.557
Who's a risk?

21:33.657 --> 21:35.500
Who's a problem that you're trying to avoid?

21:37.984 --> 21:42.853
But look, God's people are not called to decide who qualifies for love.

21:43.895 --> 21:48.242
We are to become people who move towards suffering without calculating worthiness.

21:49.538 --> 21:52.242
And Scripture makes it clear who we're called to move toward.

21:52.262 --> 21:57.750
James 2, right here, it identifies, a brother or sister among us whose poorly clothed and lacking in food.

21:58.031 --> 21:59.252
God says, go there.

21:59.813 --> 22:00.294
I love them.

22:02.057 --> 22:06.884
And in Scripture, consistently names groups of people who are rejected or marginalized.

22:07.625 --> 22:14.155
The poor, the widow, the orphan, the foreigner, the sick, the condemned, the exploited.

22:14.175 --> 22:17.680
The very people our culture is most tempted to pass by.

22:17.940 --> 22:19.122
God says, I love them.

22:19.490 --> 22:19.870
Go there.

22:22.193 --> 22:26.557
Jesus commands love for his enemies and then he models it on the cross.

22:26.697 --> 22:27.738
God says, go there.

22:27.778 --> 22:28.979
I love them.

22:31.542 --> 22:36.907
We move towards the need without pre-selection because you will never meet somebody that God doesn't love.

22:39.129 --> 22:48.498
And then Matthew 25, it reminds us that when we do that, when we feed the hungry and clothe the naked and welcome the stranger or visit the sick, ultimately we are serving Christ himself.

22:51.394 --> 22:58.947
Connects in Christ, we serve as participants in God's mission, and we seek the welfare and the peace of the city that we are in.

23:00.509 --> 23:10.346
James 2, it's a description of needs that arise in God's house with brothers or sisters, but it's clear that this heart doesn't just stay here.

23:11.307 --> 23:14.473
We gather for worship, we scatter for mission throughout the city.

23:15.234 --> 23:17.778
I wanna ask quickly, how many people in here are missionaries?

23:19.554 --> 23:21.536
Trick question, it's all of you.

23:21.576 --> 23:25.199
You should have seen that coming.

23:28.503 --> 23:31.906
Listen, ultimately, you are here because God has sent you here.

23:32.567 --> 23:37.711
And if God has sent you here, you are a missionary in Los Angeles for however long God has you here.

23:38.853 --> 23:40.915
Have that mentality, have that posture.

23:41.015 --> 23:45.219
You are in Los Angeles because God has called you to live in the city for him.

23:46.320 --> 23:47.481
And we've talked about this before.

23:47.801 --> 23:48.722
Most people,

23:49.026 --> 23:53.853
come to Los Angeles or live in Los Angeles asking, what can I get from this place?

23:54.393 --> 23:55.555
We ask a different question.

23:56.015 --> 23:56.716
What can I give?

23:57.798 --> 23:58.639
Who can I love?

23:59.460 --> 24:01.082
Where can I serve?

24:03.065 --> 24:07.511
We're not, God's people are not against the city, we're in the city, we are for the city.

24:09.113 --> 24:11.817
We're partnering with God as participants in his mission.

24:12.358 --> 24:15.602
And so that means we want to see hurting people healed.

24:16.482 --> 24:18.585
We wanna see broken people restored.

24:18.625 --> 24:24.114
We wanna see people who are lost in the kingdom of darkness saved and brought to the kingdom of light.

24:25.076 --> 24:25.977
That is our desire.

24:26.699 --> 24:28.562
And so listen, we're not here to avoid.

24:29.583 --> 24:32.047
We're not scared of the seculars out there, okay?

24:34.010 --> 24:40.581
We seek the good of our neighbor and we seek the good of our city even when it feels like they're not returning the favor.

24:42.664 --> 24:43.666
Because when the church

24:43.778 --> 24:46.942
serves with this kind of living faith that James is talking about.

24:47.563 --> 24:50.988
With sacrificial love, we become a living testimony.

24:51.288 --> 24:55.534
We become this demonstrated witness to Christ, to the world around us.

24:57.798 --> 25:01.683
Our serving doesn't just help the world, it reveals God to them.

25:03.405 --> 25:06.930
A living faith shows we serve a living savior.

25:09.294 --> 25:12.498
Okay, next, in Christ, we serve with endurance.

25:13.794 --> 25:19.500
James here in James 2, he's not rebuking someone who like occasionally forgot to help.

25:19.520 --> 25:20.981
He's not just getting on somebody's case.

25:21.021 --> 25:21.722
That's not the point.

25:23.003 --> 25:27.528
He is describing a particular moment, but what he's confronting is a pattern in people's lives.

25:28.569 --> 25:33.534
And so living faith, it doesn't produce just these random bursts of kindness.

25:34.575 --> 25:37.478
It produces a consistent embodied love for people.

25:38.599 --> 25:42.002
And so faith that's alive will show up again

25:42.242 --> 25:47.127
and again and again, because it's not a project to accomplish.

25:47.188 --> 25:48.269
It's not a box to check.

25:48.869 --> 25:50.852
It's a posture we want to cultivate over time.

25:53.034 --> 25:58.300
Scripture tells us this kind of service that we're talking about, sacrificial service requires endurance.

25:59.021 --> 26:03.566
Galatians 6, beginning of verse 9, it says, and let us not grow weary of doing good.

26:04.487 --> 26:07.851
For in due season, we will reap if we do not give up.

26:08.872 --> 26:10.834
So then, as we have opportunity,

26:10.914 --> 26:15.920
do good to everyone, and especially to those who are of the household of faith.

26:17.562 --> 26:22.949
And this passage assumes something that's kind of awkward to admit, but we should acknowledge it.

26:23.630 --> 26:26.413
Doing good does get exhausting sometimes.

26:27.334 --> 26:27.695
It's hard.

26:29.076 --> 26:33.642
Serving people can be messy, and it can be slow and unpredictable.

26:35.444 --> 26:37.827
Sometimes, maybe a lot of times, you don't see change.

26:38.909 --> 26:40.050
You're not gonna get thanked.

26:40.962 --> 26:44.946
Sometimes you invest years and years in wonder, God, is anything happening at all?

26:46.448 --> 26:47.830
But God says, don't grow weary.

26:49.231 --> 26:49.752
Don't grow weary.

26:49.772 --> 26:55.378
The gospel will free you to endure because we are not serving to get a quick result today.

26:56.319 --> 27:00.704
We're serving, trusting that God will produce eternal fruit, even if we don't get to see it.

27:03.707 --> 27:07.692
Most brokenness is not solved in a moment.

27:08.833 --> 27:09.714
It's healing.

27:10.274 --> 27:12.097
through faithful presence over time.

27:14.200 --> 27:17.185
Scripture promises that kind of endurance is not wasted, right?

27:17.205 --> 27:19.969
In due season, we will reap if we do not give up.

27:20.871 --> 27:21.892
So we serve with endurance.

27:25.037 --> 27:31.046
Next in Christ, we serve by meeting real needs, both physical and spiritual.

27:32.288 --> 27:37.236
This is where James 2 is just screaming out at us with convicting clarity, okay?

27:37.256 --> 27:38.418
Scripture never

27:38.498 --> 27:42.984
forces us to choose between caring for someone's soul and caring for their body.

27:44.185 --> 27:45.948
It's not a binary choice that we have to make.

27:46.508 --> 27:48.631
Our incarnate God cares about both.

27:50.974 --> 27:56.060
And so we believe that a person's ultimate need is salvation in Jesus, yes.

27:56.581 --> 27:59.825
But that doesn't discount or diminish their physical needs at all.

28:01.527 --> 28:03.490
It means that when someone's hungry, feed them.

28:04.972 --> 28:06.674
When someone's hurting, comfort them.

28:07.714 --> 28:10.178
If they're lonely, see them, be with them.

28:11.079 --> 28:13.883
And when someone is spiritually lost, point them to Jesus.

28:15.125 --> 28:17.248
Those are not separate missions.

28:17.429 --> 28:19.552
That is one gospel mission.

28:20.754 --> 28:26.803
Really helpful way that I've heard it described is that the world suffers from both physical and spiritual hunger.

28:27.724 --> 28:34.795
And the holistic mission of God's people is to satisfy both of those hungers through the bread of life and through loaves of bread.

28:36.217 --> 28:37.138
I love that picture.

28:38.434 --> 28:41.078
This is why the ministry at Serve LA matters.

28:42.360 --> 28:46.005
Serve LA is what compassion looks like when it follows through.

28:46.045 --> 29:03.730
We're talking about 70,000 plus meals a year, hundreds of showers and services for the whole person, right, from clothing to housing resources to medical care, guiding people from a place of suffering to flourishing,

29:04.290 --> 29:11.577
And physical needs are being met for some of the most vulnerable people in our city, but the heartbeat has always been deeper than that.

29:12.618 --> 29:14.940
It's always been about being more than a meal.

29:16.421 --> 29:17.262
It's learning a name.

29:18.483 --> 29:22.387
It's making eye contact with people who have been made invisible in Los Angeles.

29:23.588 --> 29:26.891
It's asking to hear somebody's story and praying for them.

29:28.373 --> 29:34.098
It's affirming dignity before seeing need, but then also meeting the needs of the soul and the body.

29:35.234 --> 29:36.696
Bread of life loaves of bread.

29:37.717 --> 29:38.458
Christ offers both.

29:40.662 --> 29:47.751
And then finally, in Christ, we serve blessing others, but also being blessed by serving as well.

29:49.614 --> 29:52.578
When we serve, God often blesses us through it too.

29:53.219 --> 29:55.222
It's a classic God too for one situation.

29:57.605 --> 30:01.170
Classic.

30:01.442 --> 30:10.294
God forms us as we serve, and He allows us to experience the blessings of Christ in ways that we honestly might otherwise miss.

30:11.435 --> 30:17.824
I see this all over the place, but one that holds a special place in my heart is I see this every year at Royal Family Kids camp.

30:18.925 --> 30:20.067
Yes, at the camp.

30:20.367 --> 30:25.554
It's this a camp for children who are part of the foster care system here in Los Angeles.

30:25.954 --> 30:34.226
We have about 600 catchphrases that we use every year, but one that stuck with me is we always say, campus for the campers, campus for the campers, but no one comes home unchanged.

30:36.269 --> 30:41.938
You go there to pour out for others, but God shaped your heart in unmatched ways as you do.

30:43.680 --> 30:48.728
Sign up for camp in March.

30:48.948 --> 30:53.074
So sacrificial service, it's gonna cost you something, but at the same time,

30:53.602 --> 30:56.025
Serving has a particular way of setting people free.

30:57.667 --> 31:06.619
There's a study from Columbia University that found out that volunteering was associated with up to a 43% reduction in depression risk amongst participants.

31:06.639 --> 31:13.969
And a 90% of the volunteers said that serving helped them build meaningful relationships in a stronger sense of purpose in their life.

31:15.551 --> 31:18.535
But listen, that's not just psychology, that's design.

31:19.156 --> 31:20.017
That's how God made us.

31:21.339 --> 31:23.602
You're created to love God and to love your neighbor.

31:24.034 --> 31:29.920
And so when you live in that calling, you will continue to become the person that God has designed you to be.

31:32.022 --> 31:33.543
And we're to do this together.

31:33.583 --> 31:35.685
God calls us to serve together.

31:36.406 --> 31:40.010
New Testament describes the church as a body, right?

31:40.830 --> 31:41.911
One body of different members.

31:42.212 --> 31:46.696
So we have different gifts, different strengths, different roles, but we have one mission.

31:48.077 --> 31:49.259
It's just gonna happen in different ways.

31:50.540 --> 31:51.461
We serve together, right?

31:51.521 --> 31:52.722
Some people are gonna teach.

31:53.090 --> 31:54.291
Some are going to make meals.

31:55.152 --> 31:56.594
Some are going to lift heavy objects.

31:57.334 --> 31:58.516
Some are going to lift light objects.

31:59.917 --> 32:00.858
Some are going to hold babies.

32:01.459 --> 32:05.123
That might be the light object that you lift, depending on the baby.

32:09.127 --> 32:11.209
Some people are going to bear, bird, whatever it is.

32:11.509 --> 32:12.250
We need everyone.

32:12.370 --> 32:13.331
Everyone has a part.

32:14.252 --> 32:15.353
This is not just for leaders.

32:15.473 --> 32:17.616
This is not just for the spiritually mature.

32:17.636 --> 32:18.356
This is everyone.

32:18.717 --> 32:19.858
We all have a part.

32:20.834 --> 32:28.302
And if you ever want to feel connected to the body of Christ, one of the most powerful ways you can do, you can do that, is serving alongside it.

32:29.864 --> 32:37.793
Discipleship and friendship aren't just happening in these rows and in our small groups, they happen as we serve.

32:37.813 --> 32:45.522
Okay, so we know who we are in Christ, we know what that makes us, and we know what that is meant to produce.

32:45.730 --> 32:48.553
But James doesn't let this just stay theoretical.

32:48.613 --> 32:51.456
So what does this look like for us today?

32:53.518 --> 32:57.843
At the beginning of this series on Vision Sunday, we took a survey of the church.

32:58.363 --> 33:01.927
And one of the questions was, do you regularly serve in any capacity?

33:02.688 --> 33:03.809
And we have the results.

33:05.871 --> 33:07.814
I feel like Steve Cornaki right now, like tight district.

33:09.776 --> 33:12.018
It's an election, I joke.

33:14.626 --> 33:21.115
So about 53% of the church said yes, I serve in some capacity in Los Angeles, 47% said no.

33:21.996 --> 33:25.541
So about half the people here say that they don't serve in some capacity.

33:26.602 --> 33:30.668
But give me a couple minutes, I actually think that number can change.

33:32.230 --> 33:39.340
Because even though the same faith that saves us, sends us all, it doesn't send us all in the same exact way.

33:40.621 --> 33:41.202
And that's good.

33:42.274 --> 33:46.641
The faith that James 2 is describing, it produces the same posture for everyone.

33:46.661 --> 33:52.050
We're all to be sacrificial servants, but it's expressed in a multitude of different ways.

33:53.152 --> 33:56.858
And so what I want to invite us to do is ask two primary questions today.

33:57.639 --> 33:58.440
Two primary questions.

33:58.520 --> 33:59.282
The first one is this.

34:00.043 --> 34:06.694
What are you already doing that God is inviting you to approach with the posture of sacrificial service?

34:07.855 --> 34:09.458
What are you already doing?

34:10.402 --> 34:12.664
that God is inviting you to reframe your posture.

34:14.326 --> 34:16.428
Because here's what we miss often.

34:17.149 --> 34:18.571
You are already on God's mission.

34:19.312 --> 34:20.032
We've talked about that.

34:20.373 --> 34:24.037
God is already present in the spaces that you occupy.

34:24.057 --> 34:25.859
So serve him there.

34:27.560 --> 34:36.210
Faithful servant, faithful service in God's kingdom, it's not measured by your visibility or by your platform or by your numerical impact.

34:36.370 --> 34:38.112
It's measured by love and obedience.

34:38.733 --> 34:40.114
And so you can serve

34:40.322 --> 34:46.891
Whether it feels significant or unnoticed knowing that your service matters to God wherever you are.

34:48.814 --> 34:52.439
And this posture should reframe some things for us.

34:54.121 --> 34:59.748
Some people here have capacities and have limitations that are unavoidable and that are real.

35:00.069 --> 35:06.738
It could be a stage of life, it could be physical limitations, it could be this nontraditional schedule that you have, whatever it is.

35:07.266 --> 35:11.712
But this question, this posture, combats the idea that you can't serve.

35:11.972 --> 35:12.333
You can't.

35:13.254 --> 35:14.095
Everyone can serve.

35:15.296 --> 35:25.069
And so what if you started thinking of your job, not just as a way to make money or to make impact, but as an opportunity to serve the Lord and to serve other people?

35:27.212 --> 35:35.282
What if your parenting wasn't just survival mode, but it was your opportunity for sacred service in this season of life?

35:37.026 --> 35:43.613
So what if your commute, what if your schedule, what if your routine became places of living faithfulness?

35:45.916 --> 35:50.240
This shows up in a thousand seemingly ordinary ways in our lives.

35:52.483 --> 35:57.268
So can you lead with the mind and heart of Christ in any space you find yourself in?

35:57.348 --> 36:06.418
In a community group, as a little league team coach, as a member of the PTA or a board that you sit on, can you lead with the mind and heart of Christ?

36:07.618 --> 36:16.847
Can you adjust your schedule a little bit to make room in your life and in your home and in your table and in your rhythms to create belonging for other people?

36:19.310 --> 36:23.955
It shows up in your caring for your children or for your aging parents or for a friend who's sick.

36:26.197 --> 36:35.186
It shows up when you're sitting quietly with friends who are in grief or being generous with your time and your money if you can't physically be somewhere.

36:35.842 --> 36:38.105
or advocating for those who don't have a voice.

36:38.966 --> 36:44.893
So ask this question, what am I already doing that I can approach with the posture of sacrificial service?

36:46.314 --> 36:54.104
I think of my friend and yours, my dear friend Magenna, she was telling me about her little Bible bus that she has on Tuesday nights as she calls it.

36:54.904 --> 37:02.994
She was already driving her daughters to youth group, that wasn't a new thing, but she asked the Lord, like help me to reframe this with a heart of service.

37:03.266 --> 37:08.572
And so she's asking, what if I can pick up a couple other students on the way and care for some families in that way?

37:09.614 --> 37:15.100
What if these 15 minutes in the car could look like intentional discipleship?

37:15.180 --> 37:17.804
She wasn't adding something extraordinary to her schedule.

37:18.525 --> 37:21.789
She just let living faith reshape what she was already doing.

37:24.472 --> 37:25.233
And here's the key with this.

37:25.833 --> 37:31.380
You don't need to immediately rush over there before you pay attention to right here.

37:31.901 --> 37:32.882
What's right in front of us?

37:33.122 --> 37:34.924
Who is sitting next to you right now?

37:35.845 --> 37:36.426
Who you can serve?

37:37.767 --> 37:39.889
Who is already in front of you in your life?

37:40.450 --> 37:43.974
Who's cold, hungry, lonely, unseen?

37:44.014 --> 37:51.221
Are you paying attention to what you are already doing and how God might be inviting you to serve Him as you're doing it?

37:53.244 --> 37:55.206
Don't need to stuff your schedule with a bunch of whole new things.

37:55.446 --> 37:56.988
How can you serve where God has you right now?

37:57.188 --> 37:57.568
Start there.

37:59.330 --> 38:02.994
Okay, but then you have to ask a second question, arguably a harder question for our hearts.

38:03.842 --> 38:10.612
The second question, where is God calling you to go and costly service for his kingdom and his people?

38:13.056 --> 38:17.904
Because Jesus doesn't just ask people to serve where they have time or when they feel ready.

38:19.426 --> 38:21.549
He asks people to do things that are inconvenient.

38:22.971 --> 38:27.037
He pulled fishermen off a boat mid-career, literally in the middle of their shift.

38:27.839 --> 38:30.002
He said, follow me.

38:32.226 --> 38:35.931
He sent disciples out before they felt sufficiently trained up to do the job.

38:38.575 --> 38:43.642
You were to go where and when Jesus says go, not just when it's convenient for you.

38:45.404 --> 38:50.271
No one, we're not gonna just naturally drift into serventhood.

38:51.032 --> 38:51.953
It's not how we're wired.

38:52.834 --> 38:58.382
It's gonna require intentional resistance to our natural desires for comfort and for ease.

38:58.702 --> 39:01.426
And so ask, God, where are you calling me?

39:01.666 --> 39:07.173
to sacrificially count the cost for the good of another and for participation in your mission.

39:08.836 --> 39:22.254
And then be prepared because this is going to demand that you reshape your schedule or your PTO, your wallet, your rhythms, your plans, things are gonna need to change.

39:24.156 --> 39:27.841
And just like the other category, there's a thousand different ways that this can happen.

39:28.142 --> 39:31.346
I literally cannot name them all, so this is not an exhaustive list.

39:31.458 --> 39:36.827
But here's a few needs that we've identified as a church that I'd love for you to consider as you're asking God about this.

39:37.428 --> 39:38.570
First is Sundays.

39:39.832 --> 39:56.079
Here, we're here to gather on Sundays, but should some of my Sundays look a little different so I can serve my fellow sisters and brothers, can I get up a little earlier to set up the space or stay a little bit later to tear down or serve as an usher during our gatherings?

39:56.099 --> 39:58.162
Those are all pressing needs that we have right now.

39:59.586 --> 40:05.052
Or can I seek to disciple the children in our church by being a kid's or a preteen or youth volunteer?

40:07.314 --> 40:07.615
You can.

40:09.457 --> 40:10.157
And so can you.

40:10.217 --> 40:15.563
All these things.

40:15.583 --> 40:20.769
Can I create parking spaces for someone who hasn't heard the gospel to come and hear good news?

40:21.970 --> 40:23.211
It's not over spiritualizing.

40:24.032 --> 40:29.458
Can I do these things even if it costs me two Sundays a month looking the same as it does right now?

40:30.626 --> 40:32.510
Lord, is this how I can serve your people?

40:33.071 --> 40:34.114
And for some of you, it is.

40:34.174 --> 40:35.296
And for some people, it's not.

40:35.336 --> 40:35.857
That's okay.

40:36.559 --> 40:38.503
But some people aren't even considering it.

40:39.605 --> 40:40.347
And you need to ask.

40:42.692 --> 40:45.819
And it's not just serving one another inside the house.

40:45.859 --> 40:47.863
Servants on God's mission seek the good of the city.

40:48.044 --> 40:48.805
We talked about that.

40:49.206 --> 40:50.930
And so we have mission partners.

40:51.106 --> 40:57.556
who are witnessing to Christ in word and indeed throughout Los Angeles and who we wanna partner with in a variety of different ways.

40:58.037 --> 41:02.724
And we're gonna take time throughout the year to highlight them here on Sundays and online.

41:03.205 --> 41:11.599
But you can go to the webpage, you can learn all about how we have partners who are seeking restoration across the city and see how you can serve with them on mission in Los Angeles.

41:13.001 --> 41:16.306
And then as a church, we've asked God to show us

41:16.450 --> 41:21.134
Where has the shalom of the city been most fractured in Los Angeles?

41:21.755 --> 41:34.627
And God, how are you uniquely calling us, this body of believers, to step in in a few specific spaces and to seek deep, compassionate, sustained service for our city?

41:35.328 --> 41:37.450
And he's revealed two priorities for us in that.

41:38.131 --> 41:40.433
First is we are to feed and clothe the poor.

41:41.434 --> 41:43.956
And the primary way that's going to happen is through the Ministry of Serve LA.

41:45.138 --> 41:45.618
So come.

41:46.018 --> 41:47.139
Come and prep a meal.

41:47.640 --> 41:48.360
Set tables.

41:48.981 --> 41:49.762
Serve meals.

41:49.862 --> 41:51.023
Help with the shower ministry.

41:51.063 --> 41:54.287
Sit and connect with neighbors who come through.

41:55.328 --> 41:56.529
Peel some artichokes together.

41:56.569 --> 42:06.200
Really get to the heart.

42:06.220 --> 42:07.481
Fellow pastor, how dare you.

42:11.225 --> 42:12.306
But we aren't...

42:13.634 --> 42:15.436
That's the first area we do.

42:15.456 --> 42:18.641
We want to feed and clothe the poor, and the primary way that's going to happen is through ServLA.

42:19.101 --> 42:21.344
Secondly, we're called to care for the orphan.

42:21.885 --> 42:26.391
And that's primarily going to look like serving in foster care spaces, for us as a church.

42:26.411 --> 42:37.225
And foster care is a prime example of how we can have the same posture of sacrificial service, but a ton of different expressions of what that looks like.

42:37.246 --> 42:43.634
So most people, to be honest, I think most of us will hear foster care and say, I either become a foster parent or I can't really be involved.

42:44.226 --> 42:48.773
That's kind of the dichotomy we give ourselves, but that couldn't be further from the truth.

42:48.793 --> 42:53.801
Okay, there are so many different access points for sacrificially serving in this way.

42:54.863 --> 42:58.028
And so some people will foster children and we praise God for that.

42:58.990 --> 43:01.113
And I don't want you to assume that that's not you.

43:01.273 --> 43:01.894
That might be you.

43:02.776 --> 43:03.717
Earnestly pray for that.

43:05.140 --> 43:11.570
But other people are gonna participate by being a counselor or a mentor through RFKC.

43:12.130 --> 43:16.895
Other people are gonna become a host family for a weekend so they can give respite care to some bio-parents.

43:18.196 --> 43:23.661
Other people will join with a mission partner and help intercede before child services even need to be part of the equation.

43:25.363 --> 43:29.507
Other people can make a meal or do laundry once a week for a family who is fostering.

43:29.927 --> 43:31.348
Other people can pray.

43:31.388 --> 43:33.430
Everyone has a role.

43:34.271 --> 43:35.292
Everyone can participate.

43:37.114 --> 43:38.175
So I wanna close with this.

43:40.197 --> 43:41.458
Some people here

43:41.634 --> 43:43.757
today simply need to be encouraged.

43:44.558 --> 43:48.564
You are serving faithfully and sacrificially, so keep going.

43:49.586 --> 43:50.267
Indoor well.

43:51.869 --> 43:53.712
Don't grow weary of doing good.

43:55.314 --> 43:56.035
Serve unto the Lord.

43:56.416 --> 44:01.964
Ask Him today, Lord, refresh my heart, to serve not out of a place of obligation, but out of a place of joy.

44:04.347 --> 44:09.074
Other people here, as we talked about, are serving, but don't even realize it.

44:10.690 --> 44:19.802
And perhaps what you need today is to ask God to help you look at your life through the lens of serving and ask, how can I do what I'm doing right now unto the Lord?

44:22.085 --> 44:24.188
And then some people here just aren't serving at all.

44:25.549 --> 44:29.995
And what you hear, what you need to hear today, please do not hear any sort of shame or guilt.

44:30.676 --> 44:31.637
That's not what you need to hear.

44:32.559 --> 44:35.122
You don't need shame or guilt, but you do need to be challenged a little bit.

44:36.610 --> 44:41.756
Some of you need to remember, the king of the universe got off of the throne in heaven to serve you.

44:42.737 --> 44:45.000
So it may be time to get off your couch and serve him.

44:46.461 --> 44:46.622
Okay?

44:48.083 --> 44:48.764
There's no shame.

44:48.784 --> 44:49.725
It's just time to join the game.

44:49.785 --> 44:54.831
To live within your identity as a servant of God.

44:54.851 --> 45:00.738
And the wrong question for any of us to ask, walking out of here, is, am I doing enough?

45:01.118 --> 45:02.660
That's not the question you need to be asked.

45:02.780 --> 45:04.242
It's not a checklist to accomplish.

45:04.738 --> 45:06.220
It's a heart God wants to cultivate.

45:06.480 --> 45:08.462
So instead, start with this question.

45:08.663 --> 45:12.687
God, how do you want to shape my heart to step into what you're already calling me to do?

45:14.409 --> 45:17.273
How do you want to shape my heart to step into what you're calling me to do?

45:18.655 --> 45:30.449
Help us to assume this identity, and then from that place, there are a variety, a veritable cornucopia of ways to serve and live out that identity.

45:30.969 --> 45:31.730
I looked into it.

45:31.842 --> 45:35.388
There are roughly 50 bajillion ways to serve in Los Angeles.

45:37.131 --> 45:37.772
Okay?

45:37.792 --> 45:38.914
There is an outlet for you.

45:38.934 --> 45:40.777
And there's needs.

45:40.817 --> 45:44.864
There's needs that we have been drawn towards together as a local body of believers.

45:44.884 --> 45:45.265
You heard them.

45:45.385 --> 45:46.006
I talked about them.

45:46.246 --> 45:48.690
That may be a starting point for you if that's how you want to serve.

45:50.333 --> 45:53.298
But I'm not going to tell you what to do.

45:53.338 --> 45:55.101
That's not the point of this sermon.

45:55.362 --> 45:57.906
You ask God what He wants you to do.

45:59.074 --> 46:03.742
If it's here on Sundays, or if it's one of our church ministries, like in community groups or gospel care, great.

46:04.784 --> 46:07.889
If it's RFKC, or ServLA, or mission partners, great.

46:08.991 --> 46:11.355
If it's starting in your home, great.

46:12.877 --> 46:17.585
If it's at work, or with your neighbor, or in your margins, or somewhere you don't even know, great.

46:18.587 --> 46:19.609
That's a great place to start.

46:19.709 --> 46:22.834
Whatever you're called to do, do it sacrificially.

46:23.736 --> 46:25.138
Do it with a new identity.

46:25.954 --> 46:32.502
Do it affirming the dignity of those around you and do it with endurance, all for the glory of God and for the welfare of our city.

46:33.964 --> 46:45.738
And do this empowered by the Holy Spirit of God, not just as proclaimers of a blessing, but with a living faith, participating in good works unto the Lord.

46:45.978 --> 46:46.258
Amen.

46:47.079 --> 46:47.700
Amen, let's pray.

46:51.184 --> 46:52.786
Father in heaven, we love you.

46:53.346 --> 46:58.854
We love you and that is our prayer, God, that you would empower us by your spirit to be a people of living faith.

47:00.277 --> 47:08.189
People who are ready to count the cost and to give ourselves just as you have given yourself for us, God.

47:09.631 --> 47:21.970
And so we pray, help us to live in this identity that you've already given to us as children of God and as servants of the Most High and help us to serve your people in your city with joy, God.

47:22.978 --> 47:25.064
We love you and we pray these things in your name, Jesus.

47:28.013 --> 47:33.650
Amen.

